message.content: A 16-year-old Caucasian male with a past medical history of recurrent respiratory infections presents with chronic cough, wheezing, and difficulty breathing, and is ultimately diagnosed with cystic fibrosis.
A 16-year-old Caucasian female with a history of recurrent pulmonary infections presents with chronic cough, wheezing, and difficulty breathing, and is ultimately diagnosed with cystic fibrosis.

A 16-year-old Caucasian female with a history of recurrent respiratory infections presents with increasing shortness of breath, chronic cough, and failure to thrive, ultimately diagnosed with cystic fibrosis.
A 17-year-old Caucasian female with a history of recurrent pulmonary infections presents with chronic cough, shortness of breath, and malnutrition, with a family history of cystic fibrosis.
